  "texts": [
    "When discussing the structure of the IKS state below, we will exclusively work in the boosted frame; one can obtain the projectors in the unboosted frame viaP k,k ′ = e τz 2 qIVC• -→ ∇k Pk,k ′ e τz 2 qIVC• ← - ∇ k ′, (106)where q IVC is the IVC boost vector, and ← -∇ k ′ denotes gradient against k ′ acting on expression to the left.",
    "Note that although Pk,k ′ is diagonal in k-space, the k-space boost encoded by- → ∇ k and ← - ∇ k ′ renders P k,k ′ off-diagonal.",
    "Initialization and OptimizationSince the one-particle density matrix in the boosted frame is again diagonal in k and s, we can use the same discussion as in Section 3.3.3 when constructing the initial density matrix.",
    "Furthermore, to optimize over possible IVC spirals, we treat q IVC as a variational parameter.",
    "We perform a set of HF calculations (with multiple types of initial states if necessary) for each value of q IVC, and choose the value of q IVC with the lowest energy if we are interested in the ground state."
